20/05/2004
STRASBOURG, France -- Turkish Parliament Speaker Bulent Arinc met on Wednesday (19 May) with his Armenian counterpart, Artur Bagdasaryan, on the sidelines of the Council of Europe parliament speakers' conference in Strasbourg. The two officials focused on the Armenian-Azerbaijani conflict over Nagorno-Karabakh.
That dispute was also the topic of a meeting Tuesday between Turkish Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul and Azerbaijani President Ilham Aliyev on the sidelines of the Turkey-EU Association Council meeting. In addition, they discussed ways to strengthen bilateral relations.
On Wednesday, meanwhile, Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan arrived in Bucharest on an official visit. He and Romanian counterpart Adrian Nastase will sign a memorandum of understanding and co-operation in the field of business relations. (Anadolu Agency, NTV, TRT 2, Rompres - 19/05/04)
